standpoint /ˈstændˌpɔɪnt/

(standpoints) 

1. N-COUNT From a particular standpoint means looking at an event, situation, or idea in a particular way. 观点; 角度 

例： He believes that from a military standpoint, the situation is under control. 他认为从军事角度来看，局势已得到控制。

